&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post: Specialist Dietitian &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: Nutrition &amp; Dietetics                  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working pattern: 1.0wte&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting new post provides an opportunity to specialise in the field of home enteral nutrition and stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post graduate clinical experience in stroke and/or enteral tube feeding is preferable but applications from less experienced dietitians who are keen to learn and take on new responsibilities will also be considered. Teamwork, flexibility and excellent communication skills are essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based from the Royal Hampshire County Hospital.  The role is varied and will include: delivering a dietetic service to adult stroke service; community rehabilitation ward and supporting the wider adult team for inpatient reviews, cover for ICU and complex surgical patients may also be required. To be a liaison between community and acute teams for home enteral nutrition patients, linking in with complex discharge planning to support artificial nutrition discharges.  Some domiciliary visits may be required and some community clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be supported by the Home Enteral Nutrition team lead. There will be opportunities to develop Trust guidelines and undertake audit projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The dietetic department consists of a team of 26 dietitians, 2 nutrition specialist nurses, 2 dietetic assistants and 2 secretaries. As a department, we are involved in student training and take students on their A, B and C placements. We are committed to appraisal and continued professional development and have excellent clerical and IT support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Elliott, Dietetic Team Lead for Adult HEN on 01962 824614 or clare.elliott@hhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
